    "plan_content": "Here is a summary of the plan. Seven new files, all inside `extensions/pulseboard/` — nothing else is modified.\n\n---\n\n## What I found exploring the codebase\n\n**Pattern source**: The Nostr extension is the best minimal reference — it has the same flat `outbound` adapter shape the spec asks for and a simple runtime store. The IRC extension contributes the `ChannelPlugin` type-cast pattern used in `index.ts`.\n\n**Key SDK surface used**:\n- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` → `createChatChannelPlugin`, `getChatChannelMeta`, `defineChannelPluginEntry`, `defineSetupPluginEntry`, `ChannelPlugin`\n- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store` → `createPluginRuntimeStore`, `PluginRuntime`\n- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result` → `attachChannelToResult`\n\n---\n\n## The seven files\n\n| File | Key content |\n|---|---|\n| `src/types.ts` | 3 user-specified interfaces + `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount` (extends with `accountId: string` — required by SDK generic constraint) |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>(\"PulseBoard runtime not initialized\")` → exports `getPulseBoardRuntime`, `setPulseBoardRuntime` |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `createChatChannelPlugin<ResolvedPulseBoardAccount>` with minimal stubs for all adapters; `getChatChannelMeta(\"pulseboard\" as any)` cast needed since `\"pulseboard\"` isn't in the `ChatChannelId` union yet |\n| `index.ts` | `defineChannelPluginEntry({ id, name, description, plugin: pulseBoardPlugin as ChannelPlugin, setRuntime })` |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `export default defineSetupPluginEntry(pulseBoardPlugin)` |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | `{ id, channels, configSchema: {} }` |\n| `package.json` | `@openclaw/pulseboard`, `type: \"module\"`, full `openclaw` block with channel metadata |\n\n**Notable callout**: `getChatChannelMeta(\"pulseboard\" as any)` is intentional — the `ChatChannelId` literal union is built from registered bundled plugins. Pulseboard gets added to that union once the plugin is registered; at authoring time the cast is the correct approach (same reason IRC does `plugin: ircPlugin as ChannelPlugin` in its index.ts).\n\n**Verification**: `pnpm tsgo` → `pnpm check` → `pnpm build`",
